A woman attends a cleansing ceremony at Buckroe Beach in Hampton, Virginia, on Aug. 24, 2019. Activities are held from Aug. 23 to 25 in commemoration of the 400th anniversary of the first African landing which occurred at Old Point Comfort in Virginia in 1619. (Photo: Xinhua)  

